column1: #Text=Beto Carrero , theme park operator , 70
#Text=Beto Carrero , a Brazilian musician turned theme park operator , died in São Paulo on Friday .
#Text=He sustained heart failure during surgery at Hospital Sírio Libanês .
#Text=His Beto Carerro World in Santa Catarina state is reported to be the largest amusement facility in Latin America .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Obituaries in the News " — Associated Press , February 2 , 2008

#Text=Archbishop Christodoulos , church leader , 69
#Text=Archbishop Christodoulos of Greece 's Orthodox Church died Monday in Athens after serving almost ten years as the church 's national leader .
#Text=The archbishop , whose actual name was Christodoulos Paraskevaides , was treated for cancer since last July .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Agence France-Presse .
#Text=" Greek Archbishop Christodoulos dies " — Turkish Daily News , January 29 , 2008
#Text=Associated Press .
#Text=" Archbishop Christodoulos , 69 : Greek church leader " — Toronto Star , January 28 , 2008
#Text=Barry Morse , actor , 89
#Text=British-born , Canadian-based actor Barry Morse died on Saturday , according to his official website .
#Text=Morse was an actor since the 1930s in his native Britain .
#Text=He moved to Canada in the 1950s where he made his first television appearances on CBC Television .
#Text=During the 1960s and 1970s , Morse was seen internationally on television , particularly his regular roles on Space : 1999 and The Fugitive .
#Text=Further details of his death are not yet available .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Ed Robertson .
#Text=" Rest in peace , Lt. Gerard " — Sidereel , February 3 , 2008
#Text=Paul G. Bens , Jr. . " R.I.P. BARRY MORSE 1918 - 2008 " — Harole Writes , February 3 , 2008
#Text=" BARRY MORSE / June 10 , 1918 - February 2 , 2008 " — Barry Morse ( official website ) , February 2 , 2008
#Text=Suharto , former Indonesian President , 86
#Text=Suharto , second president of Indonesia , has died today in a Jakarta hospital at the age of 86 .
#Text=The cause of death was announced as multiple-organ failure .
#Text=He had been in the hospital since January 4 , when he was admitted with failing kidneys , heart and lungs .
#Text=A week of national mourning was declared by President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono .

#Text=In a televised address , the current president described Suharto as " one of Indonesia 's best sons and national leaders who has done very great service to his beloved nation " and called for all Indonesians to pay their respects .
#Text=The president is to oversee a state funeral after Suharto 's body is taken to his family mausoleum in Surakarta , Central Java by a fleet of seven Air Force planes .
#Text=Suharto was born Raden Suharto on June 8 , 1921 in Kemusu Argamulja , Java , Indonesia .
#Text=He was president of Indonesia from 1967 - 1998 .
#Text=Suharto is survived by two sons and one daughter .
#Text=His eldest daughter , Tutut , said , " My father passed away peacefully .

#Text=David Kimutai Too , politician , 39 or 40
#Text=Amid Kenya 's post-election violence , Orange Democratic Movement politician David Kimutai Too was killed by police at Eldoret on Thursday .
#Text=His party condemned this situation as a politically-motivated assassination .
#Text=He was the second major Kenyan politician to be killed this week ( see Mugabe Were below ) .
#Text=Related news
#Text=" At least 45 killed in new wave of violence in Kenya " — Wikinews , January 27 , 2008
#Text=Sources
#Text=Jeffrey Gettleman .
#Text=" Second Lawmaker Is Killed as Kenya 's Riots Intensify " — New York Times , February 1 , 2008
#Text=Xan Rice , Chris McGreal .
#Text=" Kenya peace talks in disarray after killing of second opposition MP " — The Guardian , February 1 , 2008
#Text=Mugabe Were , politician , 39
#Text=Melitus Mugabe Were , a moderate Kenyan opposition Member of Parliament , was assassinated on Tuesday .
#Text=He was shot outside his home is among hundreds killed in that nation 's post-election violence .
#Text=Related news
#Text=" At least 45 killed in new wave of violence in Kenya " — Wikinews , January 27 , 2008
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Would-Be Peacemaker Killed in Kenya " — New York Times , January 30 , 2008
#Text=James Ratemo .
#Text=" Kenya : ODM MP Killed as Violence Escalates " — East African Standard , January 29 , 2008
